<subsection xml:id="subsec-identifying-points-on-the-cartesian-plane">
    <title>identifying points on the cartesian plane</title>

    <p>
        In the previous section,you learnt how to draw and label the axes on the Cartesian plane
    </p>
    <p>
        Here, you will identify points on the Cartesian plane
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{red} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Discuss as a group, but draw the Cartesian plane individually
        </p>
        <p>
            Draw as shown below
        </p>
        <image>
            <latex-image label="points-on-a-plane">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                     % Draw grid
                    \draw[very thin,gray!50] (-5,-5) grid (5,5);
                    
                    % Draw x and y axes
                    \draw[thick,->] (-5.5,0) -- (5.5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                    \draw[thick,->] (0,-5.5) -- (0,5.5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
                    
                    % Tick marks and labels
                    \foreach \x in {-5,-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4,5} {
                        \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1);
                        \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                    }

                    \foreach \y in {-5,-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4,5} {
                        \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y);
                        \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                    }

                    % Origin
                    \node[anchor=north east] at (-0.1,-0.1) {\textbf{0}};

                    % Plot points and labels
                    \fill[red] (4,3) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south west] {\textbf{P}};
                    \fill[blue] (-3,2) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south east] {\textbf{Q}};
                    \fill[green] (-4,-2) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north west] {\textbf{R}}; 
                    \fill[orange] (5,-3) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north west] {\textbf{S}};

                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
            
        </image>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Locate the points P, Q, R and S
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Write the coordninates of the points identified
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Discuss how to identify points on the Cartesian plane.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
    <p>
        <m>{\color{green} \textbf{Learning Points}}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                     Coordinates represents a pair of numbers written as <m>(x, y)</m> that represents a pointâ€™s location on the Cartesian plane.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Origin is the point where the x-axis and y-axis intersect, denoted as <m>(0,0)</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Write the coordinated of A, B, C, D, E and F as shown below.
            </p>
            <image>
                <latex-image label="x">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        % Draw grid
                        \draw[very thin,gray!50] (-5,-4) grid (5,5);
                        
                        % Draw x and y axes
                        \draw[thick,->] (-5.5,0) -- (5.5,0) node[anchor=north] {\textbf{x}};
                        \draw[thick,->] (0,-4.5) -- (0,5.5) node[anchor=east] {\textbf{y}};
                        
                        % Tick marks and labels
                        \foreach \x in {-5,-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4,5} {
                            \draw[thick] (\x,-0.1) -- (\x,0.1);
                            \node[anchor=north] at (\x,-0.2) {\textbf{\x}};
                        }

                        \foreach \y in {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4,5} {
                            \draw[thick] (-0.1,\y) -- (0.1,\y);
                            \node[anchor=east] at (-0.2,\y) {\textbf{\y}};
                        }

                        % Origin
                        \node[anchor=north east] at (-0.1,-0.1) {\textbf{0}};

                        % Plot points and labels
                        \fill[red] (3,4) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south west] {\textbf{A}};
                        \fill[blue] (-2,5) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south east] {\textbf{B}};
                        \fill[green] (-4,-3) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north east] {\textbf{C}};
                        \fill[orange] (5,-2) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north west] {\textbf{D}};
                        \fill[purple] (-3,-1) circle (3pt) node[anchor=north east] {\textbf{E}};
                        \fill[cyan] (2,5) circle (3pt) node[anchor=south west] {\textbf{F}};
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                
            </image>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            A = <m>(3,4)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            B = <m>(-2,5)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            C = <m>(-4,-3)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            D = <m>(5,-2)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            E = <m>(-3,-1)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            F = <m>(2,5)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    
</subsection>